{"key":"processedPost-12833298","value":{"id":12833298,"first":12830606,"last":12842761,"when":1277989829,"utime":"07/01/10 04:10 PM","content":"In your climate, you can make a very nice outdoor bed.&nbsp; Dig a trench as wide and long as you like and put about 3\" to 4\" of manure into it.&nbsp; Spawn with your colonized substrates or grain spawn, whatever.&nbsp; Water with a lawn sprinkler.&nbsp; Sometimes it helps to cover the area with cardboard during colonization to keep the sun off and slow down drying.&nbsp; This would be far more efficient than indoor growing.<br />RR","title":"Re: Some advice needed on what to do, thanks!","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}